did.abstract: Diaries, letters, scrapbooks, photograph albums and other materials documenting student life at Vassar College.

bioghist.head: Administrative History
bioghist.p: Vassar College was founded in 1861 and opened its doors in 1865.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: Diaries, letters, scrapbooks, photograph albums and other materials documenting student life at Vassar College.

The diaries concern life on campus, other students, classes, relationships with their professors, vacations, family news, and other subjects; some volumes have short entries on daily activities while others have longer, more reflective entries.

The letters were written by students to family, friends, and Vassar faculty, with some letters received by students from family and friends, concerning life at Vassar, their studies, social events, and family affairs.
The scrapbooks contain programs, notices, invitations, and other memorabilia compiled by students.

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research according to the regulations of the Vassar College Archives and Special Collections Library without any additional restrictions.

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
userestrict.p: Permission to quote (publish) from unpublished or previously published material must be obtained as described in the regulations of the Vassar College Archives and Special Collections Library.

altformavail.head: Other Formats
altformavail.p: Many early diaries, letters, scrapbooks, and photograph albums are available via the Vassar College Libraries' Digital Library.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Vassar College Student Materials Collection, Archives and Special Collections Library, Vassar College Libraries.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is organized into 12 series, each arranged by class year. Materials with an unknown creator or class year are filed at the end of each series.
